"n.避难所，庇护所 【英】 n. 避难所，庇护所(refu ge; shelter) 【记】 a+sylum(逮捕)→不被 逮捕→庇护所(流浪汉 露宿街头会被抓起来) n. 避难所(提供保护及安全的场所) = refuge = shelter = harborage = sanctuary 【根】a非, 无, sylum逮捕－不被逮捕－去避难所－因为流浪汉露宿街头会被抓起来 【记】读: 我赛劳模. 劳模牛吧! 一天工作24小时, 几十年如一日的奉献. 但是我赛劳模, 我比劳模还牛, 不但没日没夜的工作, 还主动请求住在避难所里, 把家腾给比我更苦的人们! 【类】refugee: asylum 难民住在收容所 【记】a + slum 贫民窟象难民营,住着许多难民 asylum (n.)  early 15c., earlier asile (late 14c.), from Latin asylum ""sanctuary,"" from Greek asylon ""refuge,"" noun use of neuter of asylos ""inviolable, safe from violence,"" especially of persons seeking protection, from a- ""without"" + syle ""right of seizure."" So literally ""an inviolable place."" General sense of ""safe or secure place"" is from 1640s; meaning ""benevolent institution to shelter some class of persons"" is from 1776."
